                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d381">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">722.2315/707: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Ecuador (<persName corresp="#p_DW1"
                            type="from">Dawson</persName>) to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Quito</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1932-11-17T11:00:00-05:00"
                            >November 17, 1932—11 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received 9 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>50. Department’s telegram No. 21, November 16, 6 p.m. The memorandum in question
                    was published here on November 14 and has been well received locally. I am
                    informed that memorandum was also transmitted the Pan American Union and the
                    League of Nations.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_DW1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Dawson</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
